The paper deals with a statistical inference problem in a non-adaptive group testing scenario, which involves binary objects and disjunctive tests. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as well as data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents a novel algorithm for solving the inference problem, which involves a holographic transformation to a normal factor graph (NFG). This technique is related to signal processing (cs.SI) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
